An inside look into the WeRateDogs Twitter Account¶

This is a brief summary of the insights gained from an anlaysis of the WeRateDogs Twitter account. WeRateDogs is a twitter account that rate's people dogs with a humorous comment about the dog.

Ratings Distribution¶

Part of the appeal of WeRateDogs is that users can rate people's dogs. Our data showed that the ratings denominators were almost always 10, while the numerators were all across the board ranging from 0 with a few outliers reaching as high as 1776! With an average rating of 1.16, the charts below shows the ratings distribution of WeRateDogs. Our histogram shows to be slightly skewed to the right meaning the most ratings given were above 10 on the numerator column, which is part of the amusement of the site. (Note, 3 outlier ratings which were above 1.4 were removed)

The boxplot below shows that ratings range from 0.8 to 1.4 with the majority of ratings falling between 1 and 1.2.

Highest Rated Dog Breed¶

Filtering ratings by dog breed provided some interesting observations. The bar chart below measures the highest rated dog breed based on average rating. What is in interesting here is that our highest rated "breed" in this case shows up as "unidentifiable".

A deeper inspection of the "unidentifiable" variable shows that when the image predictions program wasn't able to identify what kind of dog was in the photo, the cell was filled "unidentifiable". Sometimes this was happening because the dog in the picture was far away like the picture below which was marked "unidentifiable" and received a 14/10 rating.

Because the variable is so prevalent in our dataset, an interesting study would be to analyze the "unidentifiable" entries and see if there are any other common themes within the pictures. For example, are any of the dogs wearing the same piece of clothing or accessory? Or are any certain locations such as the beach or a car more common? Back to our bar chart, Bouvier Des Flandres, Saluki, and Briard show to be the top 3 highest ranking canine breeds.

Dog Stages¶

Along with a unique rating system, WeRateDogs categorizes canines in separate dog stages based on the age and life stage of the dogs. The stages in order from youngest to oldest are pupper, puppo, doggo, and fluffer. There are various metrics I could have used to measure which life stage was most popular. In the chart below, I used the amount of times the original tweet was retweeted which is the ultimate compliment that someone would like the tweet enough to retweet it to their own friends and colleagues.

Unsurprisingly, puppies, or dogs in the the "pupper" stage were by far and away the tweets that were retweeted the most with 602,196 retweets. Coming in a distant second, tweets with dogs in the "doggo" stage were retweeted 130,797 times. This is a clear indication that tweets with dogs in the "pupper" stage were most popular among WeRateDogs users.

Most Favored Tweet¶

Sticking with the theme of popular puppies, the tweet below received the most "favorites" with 149,785 users liking the tweet. The nameless Chihuaha puppy falls in line with the data in that the most favored tweet is in the pupper stage and the picture has multiple photos of the pup, which as we learned from our unidentifiable column, seems to be a favorite among WeRateDogs users.

Most Common Dog Names¶

Finally, speaking of dog names, the chart below displays the most common dog names in the WeRateDogs twitter account. The name Charlie showed up 11 times in the data. Followed by the names Oliver, Cooper, and Lucy which were found 10 times in the data.
